HEADWORD: Krait
<hw>Krait</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A very venomous snake of India (<spn>Bungarus
coeruleus</spn>), allied to the cobra. Its upper parts are bluish or
brownish black, often with narrow white streaks; the belly is
whitish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kraken</ent>⟦br⟧
